Why not? Let’s apply the Rule of Eleven. 11 – 6 = 5; we can see four higher Diamonds than the @D6 so declarer has exactly one higher Diamond. Could it be the @DA? Not really – how many declarers do you know who, faced with @DA × × opposite @DQ 8 would coldly call for dummy’s EIGHT? So the logical conclusion is that declarer does not have the @DA.|
